snippet: Officials said 160 would-be migrants tried to break into a fenced-off Spanish enclave on the North African coast on Monday.
abstract: Officials say that 160 illegal migrants tried to break into a fenced-off Spanish enclave on the North African coast; migrants tried to breach two sections of the fence between Morocco and the Spanish enclave of Melilla, with about 10 succeeding in entering Spanish territory.
lead_paragraph: Officials said 160 would-be migrants tried to break into a fenced-off Spanish enclave on the North African coast on Monday.

headline.seo: Migrants Storm Spanish Enclave on North African Coast
headline.main: Spain: Migrants Storm Enclave on North African Coast
